</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph blockId="46.[264,1323,283,790]" pageId="46" pageNumber="47">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[312,415,283,309]" pageId="46" pageNumber="47">Affinity.</emphasis>
Among the Asiatic species of the genus our new species is most similar to 
<taxonomicName authority="(Martynova)" authorityName="Potapov &amp; Babenko &amp; Fjellberg" authorityYear="2006" baseAuthorityName="Potapov &amp; Babenko &amp; Fjellberg" baseAuthorityYear="2006" box="[264,522,324,350]" class="Collembola" family="Isotomidae" genus="Scutisotoma" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Collembola" pageId="46" pageNumber="47" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="stepposa">
<emphasis box="[264,366,324,349]" italics="true" pageId="46" pageNumber="47">stepposa</emphasis>
(Martynova)
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authority="Potapov &amp; Babenko &amp; Fjellberg, 2006" authorityName="Potapov &amp; Babenko &amp; Fjellberg" authorityYear="2006" box="[579,644,324,349]" class="Collembola" family="Isotomidae" genus="Scutisotoma" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Collembola" pageId="46" pageNumber="47" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="baica" status="sp.n.">
<emphasis box="[579,644,324,349]" italics="true" pageId="46" pageNumber="47">baica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[651,710,323,349]" pageId="46" pageNumber="47">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[651,710,323,349]" pageId="46" pageNumber="47" rank="species">sp.n.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
However, the two latter species both have all lateral sensilla on Th.II set in front of the lateral macrochaeta, forming a single group. Also they have a different mucro/dens ratio and more posterior setae on manubrium and dens. 
<taxonomicName authority="Potapov &amp; Babenko &amp; Fjellberg, 2006" authorityName="Potapov &amp; Babenko &amp; Fjellberg" authorityYear="2006" class="Collembola" family="Isotomidae" genus="Scutisotoma" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Collembola" pageId="46" pageNumber="47" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="montana" status="sp.n.">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="46" pageNumber="47">S. montana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[381,440,443,469]" pageId="46" pageNumber="47">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[381,440,443,469]" pageId="46" pageNumber="47" rank="species">sp.n.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
also relates to the American species 
<taxonomicName authority="Christiansen &amp; Bellinger" authorityName="Christiansen &amp; Bellinger" authorityYear="1980" class="Entognatha" family="Isotomidae" genus="Folsomides" kingdom="Animalia" order="Collembola" pageId="46" pageNumber="47" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="teres">
<emphasis box="[920,1125,444,469]" italics="true" pageId="46" pageNumber="47">Folsomides teres</emphasis>
Christiansen &amp; Bellinger
</taxonomicName>
which has an unclear generic position. Although the original description of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Christiansen &amp; Bellinger" authorityYear="1980" class="Entognatha" family="Isotomidae" genus="Folsomides" kingdom="Animalia" order="Collembola" pageId="46" pageNumber="47" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="teres">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="46" pageNumber="47">F. teres</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
indicate several differences to 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Potapov &amp; Babenko &amp; Fjellberg" authorityYear="2006" box="[694,828,524,549]" class="Collembola" family="Isotomidae" genus="Scutisotoma" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Collembola" pageId="46" pageNumber="47" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="montana">
<emphasis box="[694,828,524,549]" italics="true" pageId="46" pageNumber="47">S. montana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, the general similarity of the two species calls for additional studies. 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Christiansen &amp; Bellinger" authorityYear="1980" box="[587,672,564,589]" class="Entognatha" family="Isotomidae" genus="Folsomides" kingdom="Animalia" order="Collembola" pageId="46" pageNumber="47" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="teres">
<emphasis box="[587,672,564,589]" italics="true" pageId="46" pageNumber="47">F.teres</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
might well be a 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Bagnall" authorityYear="1949" box="[868,1011,564,589]" class="Collembola" family="Isotomidae" genus="Scutisotoma" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Collembola" pageId="46" pageNumber="47" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[868,1011,564,589]" italics="true" pageId="46" pageNumber="47">Scutisotoma</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="46.[264,1323,283,790]" pageId="46" pageNumber="47">
Many species of the genus 
<taxonomicName authority="Stach" authorityName="Stach" authorityYear="1947" box="[629,837,604,630]" class="Collembola" family="Isotomidae" genus="Subisotoma" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Collembola" pageId="46" pageNumber="47" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[629,765,604,629]" italics="true" pageId="46" pageNumber="47">Subisotoma</emphasis>
Stach
</taxonomicName>
share essential furcal characters with our 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Potapov &amp; Babenko &amp; Fjellberg" authorityYear="2006" box="[264,366,644,669]" class="Collembola" family="Isotomidae" genus="Scutisotoma" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Collembola" pageId="46" pageNumber="47" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="montana">
<emphasis box="[264,366,644,669]" italics="true" pageId="46" pageNumber="47">montana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, but other principal characteristics are different and led us to assign 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Potapov &amp; Babenko &amp; Fjellberg" authorityYear="2006" box="[1188,1291,644,669]" class="Collembola" family="Isotomidae" genus="Scutisotoma" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Collembola" pageId="46" pageNumber="47" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="montana">
<emphasis box="[1188,1291,644,669]" italics="true" pageId="46" pageNumber="47">montana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
to 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Bagnall" authorityYear="1949" box="[264,407,684,709]" class="Collembola" family="Isotomidae" genus="Scutisotoma" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Collembola" pageId="46" pageNumber="47" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[264,407,684,709]" italics="true" pageId="46" pageNumber="47">Scutisotoma</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and not to 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Stach" authorityYear="1947" box="[539,676,684,709]" class="Collembola" family="Isotomidae" genus="Subisotoma" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Collembola" pageId="46" pageNumber="47" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[539,676,684,709]" italics="true" pageId="46" pageNumber="47">Subisotoma</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(see also remarks to 
<taxonomicName authority="Potapov &amp; Babenko &amp; Fjellberg, 2006" authorityName="Potapov &amp; Babenko &amp; Fjellberg" authorityYear="2006" box="[924,1019,684,709]" class="Collembola" family="Isotomidae" genus="Scutisotoma" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Collembola" pageId="46" pageNumber="47" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="baica" status="sp.n.">
<emphasis box="[924,1019,684,709]" italics="true" pageId="46" pageNumber="47">S. baica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1026,1085,684,710]" pageId="46" pageNumber="47">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[1026,1085,684,710]" pageId="46" pageNumber="47" rank="species">sp.n.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="46" pageNumber="47" type="distribution">
<paragraph blockId="46.[264,1323,283,790]" box="[312,1225,724,750]" pageId="46" pageNumber="47">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[312,472,724,750]" pageId="46" pageNumber="47">Distribution.</emphasis>
Known from several mountainous localities of western 
<collectingCountry box="[1129,1221,724,750]" name="Canada" pageId="46" pageNumber="47">Canada</collectingCountry>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="46.[264,1323,283,790]" box="[312,1162,764,790]" pageId="46" pageNumber="47">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[312,528,764,790]" pageId="46" pageNumber="47">Name derivation.</emphasis>
The name reflects the distribution of the new species.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
